  "title": "Explain how to design the no result experience",
  "body": "*From our customer support*\r\n\r\nWhen there is no results, we only show a simple message / template. However it could also show the results of the empty query. This is not trivial but it could help going back to a search flow for users.\r\n\r\n - [ ] First iteration: only custom template + if no result, link to clear all filters\r\n - [ ] Second iteration: go deeper, provide custom widget examples for advanced use case (current refinements, display empty search...)",
